msgstr ""
"No ``fstring_replacement_field``, se ``f_debug_specifier`` estiver presente, "
"todo espaĂ§o em branco apĂłs a chave de abertura atĂŠ o ``f_debug_specifier``, "
"bem como o espaĂ§o em branco imediatamente apĂłs o ``f_debug_specifier``, ĂŠ "
"preservado como parte da expressĂŁo."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1239
msgid ""
"The expression is not handled in the tokenization phase; it is retrieved "
"from the source code using locations of the ``{`` token and the token after "
"``=``."
msgstr ""
"A expressĂŁo nĂŁo ĂŠ tratada na fase de tokenizaĂ§ĂŁo; ela ĂŠ recuperada do cĂłdigo-"
"fonte usando as localizaĂ§Ăľes do token ``{`` token e do token apĂłs o ``=``."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1244
msgid ""
"The ``FSTRING_MIDDLE`` definition uses :ref:`negative lookaheads <lexical-"
"lookaheads>` (``!``) to indicate special characters (backslash, newline, "
"``{``, ``}``) and sequences (``f_quote``)."
msgstr ""
"A definiĂ§ĂŁo de ``FSTRING_MIDDLE`` usa :ref:`lookaheads negativos<lexical-"
"lookaheads>` (``!``) para indicar caracteres especiais (contrabarra, novas "
"linhas, ``{``, ``}``) e sequĂŞncias (``f_quote``)."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1285
msgid ""
"In the above grammar snippet, the ``f_quote`` and ``FSTRING_MIDDLE`` rules "
"are context-sensitive -- they depend on the contents of ``FSTRING_START`` of "
"the nearest enclosing ``fstring``."
msgstr ""
"No trecho de gramĂĄtica acima, as regras ``f_quote`` e ``FSTRING_MIDDLE`` sĂŁo "
"sensĂ­veis ao contexto -- elas dependem do conteĂşdo de ``FSTRING_START`` da "
"``fstring`` que envolve mais prĂłxima."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1289
msgid ""
"Constructing a more traditional formal grammar from this template is left as "
"an exercise for the reader."
msgstr ""
"A construĂ§ĂŁo de uma gramĂĄtica formal mais tradicional a partir deste modelo "
"fica como exercĂ­cio para o leitor."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1292
msgid ""
"The grammar for t-strings is identical to the one for f-strings, with *t* "
"instead of *f* at the beginning of rule and token names and in the prefix."
msgstr ""
"A gramĂĄtica para t-strings ĂŠ idĂŞntica Ă  gramĂĄtica para f-strings, com *t* em "
"vez de *f* no inĂ­cio dos nomes de regras e tokens e no prefixo."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1306
msgid "Numeric literals"
msgstr "Literais numĂŠricos"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1312
msgid ""
":data:`~token.NUMBER` tokens represent numeric literals, of which there are "
"three types: integers, floating-point numbers, and imaginary numbers."
msgstr ""
"Tokens :data:`~token.NUMBER` representam literais numĂŠricos, dos quais "
"existem trĂŞs tipos: inteiros, nĂşmeros de ponto flutuante e nĂşmeros "
"imaginĂĄrios."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1320
msgid ""
"The numeric value of a numeric literal is the same as if it were passed as a "
"string to the :class:`int`, :class:`float` or :class:`complex` class "
"constructor, respectively. Note that not all valid inputs for those "
"constructors are also valid literals."
msgstr ""
"O valor numĂŠrico de um literal numĂŠrico ĂŠ o mesmo que seria se fosse passado "
"como uma string para os construtores de classe :class:`int`, :class:`float` "
"ou :class:`complex`, respectivamente. Observe que nem todas as entradas "
"vĂĄlidas para esses construtores tambĂŠm sĂŁo literais vĂĄlidos."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1325
msgid ""
"Numeric literals do not include a sign; a phrase like ``-1`` is actually an "
"expression composed of the unary operator '``-``' and the literal ``1``."
msgstr ""
"Literais numĂŠricos nĂŁo incluem um sinal; uma frase como ``-1`` ĂŠ, na "
"verdade, uma expressĂŁo composta pelo operador unĂĄrio '``-``' e o literal "
"``1``."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1339
msgid "Integer literals"
msgstr "Inteiros literais"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1341
msgid "Integer literals denote whole numbers. For example::"
msgstr "Literais inteiros denotam nĂşmeros inteiros. Por exemplo:"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1343
msgid ""
"7\n"
"3\n"
"2147483647"
msgstr ""
"7\n"
"3\n"
"2147483647"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1347
msgid ""
"There is no limit for the length of integer literals apart from what can be "
"stored in available memory::"
msgstr ""
"NĂŁo hĂĄ limite para o comprimento de literais inteiros, exceto o que pode ser "
"armazenado na memĂłria disponĂ­vel::"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1350
msgid "7922816251426433759354395033679228162514264337593543950336"
msgstr "7922816251426433759354395033679228162514264337593543950336"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1352
msgid ""
"Underscores can be used to group digits for enhanced readability, and are "
"ignored for determining the numeric value of the literal. For example, the "
"following literals are equivalent::"
msgstr ""
"Sublinhados podem ser usados para agrupar dĂ­gitos para melhor legibilidade e "
"sĂŁo ignorados para determinar o valor numĂŠrico do literal. Por exemplo, os "
"seguintes literais sĂŁo equivalentes:"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1356
msgid ""
"100_000_000_000\n"
"100000000000\n"
"1_00_00_00_00_000"
msgstr ""
"100_000_000_000\n"
"100000000000\n"
"1_00_00_00_00_000"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1360
msgid ""
"Underscores can only occur between digits. For example, ``_123``, ``321_``, "
"and ``123__321`` are *not* valid literals."
msgstr ""
"Sublinhados sĂł podem ocorrer entre dĂ­gitos. Por exemplo, ``_123``, ``321_`` "
"e ``123__321`` *nĂŁo* sĂŁo literais vĂĄlidos."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1363
msgid ""
"Integers can be specified in binary (base 2), octal (base 8), or hexadecimal "
"(base 16) using the prefixes ``0b``, ``0o`` and ``0x``, respectively. "
"Hexadecimal digits 10 through 15 are represented by letters ``A``-``F``, "
"case-insensitive.  For example::"
msgstr ""
"Os nĂşmeros inteiros podem ser especificados em binĂĄrio (base 2), octal (base "
"8) ou hexadecimal (base 16) usando os prefixos ``0b``, ``0o`` e ``0x``, "
"respectivamente. Os dĂ­gitos hexadecimais de 10 a 15 sĂŁo representados pelas "
"letras ``A``-``F``, sem distinĂ§ĂŁo entre maiĂşsculas e minĂşsculas. Por exemplo:"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1368
msgid ""
"0b100110111\n"
"0b_1110_0101\n"
"0o177\n"
"0o377\n"
"0xdeadbeef\n"
"0xDead_Beef"
msgstr ""
"0b100110111\n"
"0b_1110_0101\n"
"0o177\n"
"0o377\n"
"0xdeadbeef\n"
"0xDead_Beef"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1375
msgid ""
"An underscore can follow the base specifier. For example, ``0x_1f`` is a "
"valid literal, but ``0_x1f`` and ``0x__1f`` are not."
msgstr ""
"Um sublinhado pode seguir o especificador base. Por exemplo, ``0x_1f`` ĂŠ um "
"literal vĂĄlido, mas ``0_x1f`` e ``0x__1f`` nĂŁo sĂŁo."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1379
msgid ""
"Leading zeros in a non-zero decimal number are not allowed. For example, "
"``0123`` is not a valid literal. This is for disambiguation with C-style "
"octal literals, which Python used before version 3.0."
msgstr ""
"Zeros Ă  esquerda em um nĂşmero decimal diferente de zero nĂŁo sĂŁo permitidos. "
"Por exemplo, ``0123`` nĂŁo ĂŠ um literal vĂĄlido. Isso serve para desambiguaĂ§ĂŁo "
"com literais octais no estilo C, que o Python usava antes da versĂŁo 3.0."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1384
msgid ""
"Formally, integer literals are described by the following lexical "
"definitions:"
msgstr ""
"Formalmente, literais inteiros sĂŁo descritos pelas seguintes definiĂ§Ăľes "
"lexicais:"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1401
#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1465
msgid "Underscores are now allowed for grouping purposes in literals."
msgstr ""
"Os sublinhados agora sĂŁo permitidos para fins de agrupamento de literais."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1412
msgid "Floating-point literals"
msgstr "Literais de ponto flutuante"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1414
msgid ""
"Floating-point (float) literals, such as ``3.14`` or ``1.5``, denote :ref:"
"`approximations of real numbers <datamodel-float>`."
msgstr ""
"Literais de ponto flutuante (float), como ``3.14`` ou ``1.5``, denotam :ref:"
"`aproximaĂ§Ăľes de nĂşmeros reais <datamodel-float>`."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1417
msgid ""
"They consist of *integer* and *fraction* parts, each composed of decimal "
"digits. The parts are separated by a decimal point, ``.``::"
msgstr ""
"Eles consistem em partes *inteiras* e *fracionĂĄrias*, cada uma composta por "
"dĂ­gitos decimais. As partes sĂŁo separadas por um ponto decimal, ``.``::"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1420
msgid ""
"2.71828\n"
"4.0"
msgstr ""
"2.71828\n"
"4.0"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1423
msgid ""
"Unlike in integer literals, leading zeros are allowed. For example, "
"``077.010`` is legal, and denotes the same number as ``77.01``."
msgstr ""
"Ao contrĂĄrio dos literais inteiros, zeros Ă  esquerda sĂŁo permitidos nas "
"partes numĂŠricas. Por exemplo, ``077.010`` ĂŠ vĂĄlido e denota o mesmo nĂşmero "
"que ``77.01``."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1426
msgid ""
"As in integer literals, single underscores may occur between digits to help "
"readability::"
msgstr ""
"Assim como em literais inteiros, sublinhados simples podem ocorrer entre "
"dĂ­gitos para ajudar na legibilidade::"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1429
msgid ""
"96_485.332_123\n"
"3.14_15_93"
msgstr ""
"96_485.332_123\n"
"3.14_15_93"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1432
msgid "Either of these parts, but not both, can be empty. For example::"
msgstr ""
"Qualquer uma dessas partes, mas nĂŁo ambas, pode estar vazia. Por exemplo:"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1434
msgid ""
"10.  # (equivalent to 10.0)\n"
".001  # (equivalent to 0.001)"
msgstr ""
"10.  # (equivalente a 10.0)\n"
".001  # (equivalente a 0.001)"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1437
msgid ""
"Optionally, the integer and fraction may be followed by an *exponent*: the "
"letter ``e`` or ``E``, followed by an optional sign, ``+`` or ``-``, and a "
"number in the same format as the integer and fraction parts. The ``e`` or "
"``E`` represents \"times ten raised to the power of\"::"
msgstr ""
"Opcionalmente, o inteiro e a fraĂ§ĂŁo podem ser seguidos por um *expoente*: a "
"letra ``e`` ou ``E``, seguida por um sinal opcional, ``+`` ou ``-``, e um "
"nĂşmero no mesmo formato das partes inteira e fracionĂĄria. O ``e`` ou ``E`` "
"representa \"dez vezes elevado Ă  potĂŞncia de\"::"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1442
msgid ""
"1.0e3  # (represents 1.0Ă10Âł, or 1000.0)\n"
"1.166e-5  # (represents 1.166Ă10âťâľ, or 0.00001166)\n"
"6.02214076e+23  # (represents 6.02214076Ă10Â˛Âł, or 602214076000000000000000.)"
msgstr ""
"1.0e3  # (representa 1.0Ă10Âł ou 1000.0)\n"
"1.166e-5  # (representa 1.166Ă10âťâľ ou 0.00001166)\n"
"6.02214076e+23  # (representa 6.02214076Ă10Â˛Âł ou 602214076000000000000000.)"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1446
msgid ""
"In floats with only integer and exponent parts, the decimal point may be "
"omitted::"
msgstr ""
"Em floats com apenas partes inteiras e expoentes, o ponto decimal pode ser "
"omitido::"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1449
msgid ""
"1e3  # (equivalent to 1.e3 and 1.0e3)\n"
"0e0  # (equivalent to 0.)"
msgstr ""
"1e3  # (equivalente a 1.e3 e 1.0e3)\n"
"0e0  # (equivalente a 0.)"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1452
msgid ""
"Formally, floating-point literals are described by the following lexical "
"definitions:"
msgstr ""
"Formalmente, literais de ponto flutuante sĂŁo descritos pelas seguintes "
"definiĂ§Ăľes lĂŠxicas:"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1474
msgid "Imaginary literals"
msgstr "Literais imaginĂĄrios"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1476
msgid ""
"Python has :ref:`complex number <typesnumeric>` objects, but no complex "
"literals. Instead, *imaginary literals* denote complex numbers with a zero "
"real part."
msgstr ""
"Python possui objetos :ref:`nĂşmero complexo <typesnumeric>`, mas nĂŁo possui "
"literais complexos. Em vez disso, *literais imaginĂĄrios* denotam nĂşmeros "
"complexos com parte real zero."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1481
msgid ""
"For example, in math, the complex number 3+4.2\\ *i* is written as the real "
"number 3 added to the imaginary number 4.2\\ *i*. Python uses a similar "
"syntax, except the imaginary unit is written as ``j`` rather than *i*::"
msgstr ""
"Por exemplo, na matemĂĄtica, o nĂşmero complexo 3+4.2\\ *i* ĂŠ escrito como o "
"nĂşmero real 3 somado ao nĂşmero imaginĂĄrio 4.2\\ *i*. Python usa uma sintaxe "
"semelhante, exceto que a unidade imaginĂĄria ĂŠ escrita como ``j`` em vez de "
"*i*::"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1486
msgid "3+4.2j"
msgstr "3+4.2j"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1488
msgid ""
"This is an expression composed of the :ref:`integer literal <integers>` "
"``3``, the :ref:`operator <operators>` '``+``', and the :ref:`imaginary "
"literal <imaginary>` ``4.2j``. Since these are three separate tokens, "
"whitespace is allowed between them::"
msgstr ""
"Esta ĂŠ uma expressĂŁo composta pelo :ref:`literal inteiro <integers>` ``3``, "
"o :ref:`operador <operators>` '``+``' e o :ref:`literal imaginĂĄrio "
"<imaginary>` ``4.2j``. Como esses sĂŁo trĂŞs tokens separados, espaĂ§os em "
"branco sĂŁo permitidos entre eles::"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1494
msgid "3 + 4.2j"
msgstr "3 + 4.2j"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1496
msgid ""
"No whitespace is allowed *within* each token. In particular, the ``j`` "
"suffix, may not be separated from the number before it."
msgstr ""
"Nenhum espaĂ§o em branco ĂŠ permitido *dentro* de cada token. Em particular, o "
"sufixo ``j`` nĂŁo pode ser separado do nĂşmero que o precede."

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1500
msgid ""
"The number before the ``j`` has the same syntax as a floating-point literal. "
"Thus, the following are valid imaginary literals::"
msgstr ""
"O nĂşmero antes do ``j`` tem a mesma sintaxe de um literal de ponto "
"flutuante. Portanto, os seguintes sĂŁo literais imaginĂĄrios vĂĄlidos:"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1503
msgid ""
"4.2j\n"
"3.14j\n"
"10.j\n"
".001j\n"
"1e100j\n"
"3.14e-10j\n"
"3.14_15_93j"
msgstr ""
"4.2j\n"
"3.14j\n"
"10.j\n"
".001j\n"
"1e100j\n"
"3.14e-10j\n"
"3.14_15_93j"

#: ../../reference/lexical_analysis.rst:1511
msgid ""
"Unlike in a floating-point literal the decimal point can be omitted if the "
"imaginary number only has an integer part. The number is still evaluated as "
"a floating-point number, not an integer::"
msgstr ""
"Ao contrĂĄrio de um literal de ponto flutuante, o ponto decimal pode ser "
